abstract = {The LETOR website contains three information retrieval datasets used as a benchmark for testing machine learning ideas for ranking. Participating algorithms are measured using standard IR ranking measures (NDCG, precision, MAP). Similarly to other participating algorithms, we train a linear classifier. In contrast, we define an additional free benchmark variable for each query. This allows expressing the fact that results for different queries are incomparable for the purpose of determining relevance. The results are slightly better yet significantly simpler than the reported participating algorithms.},
